You are working on a robotics project using ROS 2 Humble for a Yaskawa GP7 manipulator.

Project context:
- Ubuntu 22.04
- ROS 2 Humble
- MoveIt 2
- ros2_control
- Gazebo Classic (already working and must not break)
- Ignition Gazebo 6 will be added as a second simulation backend

Current workspace packages:
- gp7_description
- gp7_moveit_config
- gp7_bringup
- gp7_gazebo_classic
- gp7_task_executor
- gp7_task_executor_msgs
- gp7_vision_pipeline
- gp7_vision_bringup
- gp7_vision_gazebo_bridge
- gp7_handeye_calibration

Architecture principles:
- Do NOT redesign the whole workspace
- Reuse existing packages whenever possible
- Keep Gazebo Classic as stable baseline
- Add Ignition Gazebo as a separate new package
- Motion execution must go through MoveIt
- Do NOT directly stream joint commands
- Do NOT use queue_traj_point
- Future real robot execution will use follow_joint_trajectory with MotoROS2

Development roadmap:
1. Keep simulation stable
2. Add waypoint execution system
3. Simulate RL output using fake waypoint list
4. Visualize path and trajectory
5. Integrate RL later
6. Move to real GP7 robot

Coding style:
- Modular ROS 2 packages
- Clear separation of concerns
- Minimal changes to existing code
- Clean logging and debug-friendly
- Prefer simple working solution first

Always:
- Analyze before coding
- Propose plan before large changes
- Keep ROS 2 Humble compatibility
